     Specifying a delay (icondelay) value of 0 will cause  _k_a_l_e_i_d
     to  draw  into  its window (icon) at top speed, bogging down
     your server and, if _k_a_l_e_i_d is run  remotely,  your  network.
     The  default  delay  value was chosen to work well on a fast
     CPU with a fast X server -- it is probably too low for  many
     systems.

     If _k_a_l_e_i_d and the server are running on the same  CPU,  run-
     ning  _k_a_l_e_i_d with a higher nice (nice(1)) value will usually
     produce good results without 1) swamping the server, and  2)
     requiring you to impose an unpleasantly long delay.

